The paper focuses on the use of deep convolutional neural networks for prostate cancer detection using diffusion-weighted magnetic resonance imaging. This falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging (cs.Medical Imaging) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) applications in the medical field. The use of neural networks also falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
